<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - REAR COVER, FLYWHEEL, and POWER STEERING GEAR DRIVE -
        Installation - Rear Main Seal and Wear Sleeve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Rear Main Seal and Wear Sleeve</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When replacing the rear main seal, note that production engines will not have a wear sleeve. Wear
                    sleeves are only available as a service item included with the replacement rear main oil seal.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2651331" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0725.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 481. Rear/Wear Sleeve Installer</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Bolt Rear / Wear Sleeve Installer tool onto end of crankshaft. Make sure crankshaft
                alignment dowel fits in dowel recess hole in the installation tool.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651332" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0727.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 482. Orientation or rear main oil seal and wear sleeve</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dust seal lip</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear main oil seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft side (forward)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wear sleeve (internal bevel)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Lubricate the outer diameter of rear main oil seal with an approximate 50/50 solution of dish
                    washing soap and water prior to assembly. Do not use any other type of lubricant.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Orient seal as shown in the following graphic and slide onto installation tool.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651333" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0748.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 483. Sealant application to secondary crankshaft flange</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a 360&#176; bead of Loctite&#174; hydraulic sealant onto the rear edge of the
                secondary crankshaft flange prior to wear sleeve / oil seal installation.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651334" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0726.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 484. Rear/Wear Sleeve Installer</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Base</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear main oil seal and wear sleeve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear / Wear Sleeve Installer</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position rear main oil seal / wear sleeve combination onto the rear main oil seal / wear
                sleeve installer.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651335" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0724.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 485. Rear main oil seal and wear sleeve combination on crankshaft</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear / Wear Sleeve Installer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear main oil seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Drive nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Thrust bearing</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place thrust bearing and drive nut onto threaded shaft. Tighten nut until rear main oil seal
                bottoms out in rear oil seal carrier.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
